section.section:
"Nonpoint source pollution control project" includes:
An agricultural best management implementation practice, including cover crops, riparian forested buffer, manure processing, grassed waterways, animal waste storage structures, and livestock fencing;
An urban or suburban stormwater practice;
A sustainable forest management practice, including a forest stewardship plan or a nonornamental urban and suburban tree planting project;
Stream and wetland restoration;
Riparian buffer planting;
A project that demonstrates the effectiveness of an innovative nonpoint source pollution reduction measure provided that the measure is capable of integration into existing nonpoint source pollution programs;
Technical assistance necessary to implement a nonpoint source pollution control project;
Improvement of a municipal park located on or adjacent to a waterway, provided that the improvement is limited to state-of-the-art and sustainable nonpoint source pollution control measures that demonstrably improve water quality by reducing nitrogen, phosphorus, and sediment pollution; and
Strategic monitoring of water quality improvements from nonpoint source pollution control projects that have been funded, in whole or in part, with grants from the Trust Fund.
